Repost from @nina.fetch⁠
⁠
This self portrait shoot was inspired by the toitvolant dress I rented through nuuly. I saw it in the app, and was like “I have no idea where I will wear this but I love it and I need it.”So I came up with the reason to wear the dress 📸 and self portraits I planned turned into a dancing session and ended up being oleg.pashkovsky ‘s  first of 30 AI sketches he’s working on currently, check out the reels if you haven’t seen it! ⁠
Btw, It’s not an ad, but I wanted to share this with you, because I’ve been renting clothing for over 2 years now, and it significantly reduced the number of pieces I buy, and therefore I invest in longer lasting basics and rent any statement pieces when I’m in the mood. Another pro, you can experiment with style as much as you want. The only con of renting is that sometimes pieces can come damaged, or way worse quality than advertised. But you just gotta learn to choose, like with any online shopping. I don’t remember the last time I was disappointed with my order. ( #📷 @nina.fetch )
